Obviously, she’s most famous — or should I say, infamous — for cross-dressing. Dressing up like a man.

Somewhat unnatural, I feel. But who are we to judge?

What are you going to say about her?

Well. Fiction’s goal is not to pass judgement, necessarily. Of course, sometimes we need to offer moral guidance to our audiences, but it would be erroneous to suggest that Moll is some strange, unwell woman. Though I do hope, wherever she is, that she will consider taking a life of honesty and goodness, as opposed to petty thievery...Something more befitting of a lady, perhaps.

