<<include "header">>
<main>

Hey. Rule number 4 of being a criminal in the City...sometimes, you can stop and smell the roses. Take in your surroundings properly, make sure you can spot your nearest exit route in case the lawmen come calling...but enjoy yourself, too.

/*beat*/

I’ve thought about it, and...I think I’d want to be remembered as someone who lived truthfully. Who did the best she could with what she had. Who was loyal, and good to her friends, and helped those who needed it, and took from those who didn’t. 

You know, I’ve nothing to be ashamed of. Nothing at all. They can write what they want. I know who I am.

/*beat*/

What would you want to be remembered for? In two, three, five hundred years? Maybe think about it. Walk around this place for a little while. Take it in. Talk to your friends, your family. There’s no rush. The air is shimmering now. It’s time for me to go. But you can take your time.



</main>
